<LP>
   ATLANTA -- Delta Air Lines said June traffic fell 1.8%, to
5.43 billion revenue passenger miles from 5.53 billion in the
year-earlier period. Load factor, or the percentage of seats
filled, was 65.44%, compared with 70.98%.
   A revenue passenger mile is one paying passenger carried
one mile.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   For the year to date, the carrier said its traffic fell
1.2%, to 28.74 billion revenue passenger miles from 29.11
billion a year ago. Load factor fell to 59.64% from 64.24%.
