<LP>
   NEW YORK -- J.P. Morgan &amp; Co. replaced Earle N. Cutler as
head of its U.S. private bank, in one of several personnel
changes affecting that unit.
   John T. Lane, who until May had been a corporate banker at
Morgan, will succeed Mr. Cutler, who will become senior
marketing executive within the domestic private bank.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   In addition, Arthur Sculley, who heads private banking for
Latin America and the Middle East, will become head of a new
global asset management group within Morgan's private bank,
effective Oct. 1.
   Also, Harry Barbee will retire Oct. 1 as head of the
private bank's investment management unit. He will be
succeeded by Jean L.P. Brunel, who currently heads J.P.
Morgan Investment Management Australia Ltd.
