<HL>
   Treasury Plans to Raise
   $5.2 Billion Next Week
</HL>
<DATE>
07/05/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C15
</SO>
<IN>
CDS, INTEREST RATES, COMMERCIAL PAPER (FIN)
BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)
</IN>
<GV>
TREASURY DEPARTMENT (TRE)
</GV>
<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- The Treasury plans to raise about $5.2
billion in cash next week through sales of bills and notes.
   On Monday, it plans to raise $1.9 billion with the sale of
about $18 billion in short-term bills to redeem $16.09
billion in maturing bills. The offering will be divided
evenly between 13-week and 26-week bills maturing Oct. 11 and
Jan. 10, 1991, respectively. The bills will be available in
minimum denominations of $10,000.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   On Wednesday, the Treasury plans to raise $3.3 billion in
cash with the sale of about $8 billion in seven-year notes to
redeem $4.7 billion in maturing notes. The offering will
mature July 15. The notes will be available in minimum $1,000
denominations.
   Bids for the bills and notes must be received by 1 p.m.
EDT on the day of the auction at the Treasury or at Federal
Reserve banks or branches.
