   Business Brief -- Eastman Kodak Co.:
   Recyclable 35mm Camera
   To Be Offered by October
</HL>
<DATE>
07/05/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A3
</SO>
<CO>
   EK
</CO>
<IN>
RECREATION, ENTERTAINMENT, TOYS, MOVIES, PHOTOGRAPHY, SPORTS (REC)
</IN>
<LP>
   Eastman Kodak Co., Rochester, N.Y., said it plans to
introduce a recyclable 35mm camera, the Fun Saver 35.
   The photographic, pharmaceutical and chemical concern said
the camera, with a built-in electronic flash, will be priced
at less than $16 and available to consumers by mid-October.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Designed for indoor and outdoor use, each camera will be
sold loaded with a 24-exposure roll of Kodacolor Gold 400
print film, Kodak said. Upon completing all 24 exposures, a
user may return the entire camera to a photofinisher, who
will process the film and return the camera for recycling.
