<HL>
   Marketing Brief -- Rogers Communications Inc.:
   Company Agrees to Acquire
   Skyline Cablevision Shares
</HL>
<DATE>
07/05/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B4
</SO>
<CO>
   RCI.B
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Rogers Communications Inc. said it agreed to purchase all
the shares it doesn't already own of Skyline Cablevision
Ltd., a closely held cable television concern.
   Terms of the transaction weren't disclosed. Skyline
Cablevision, Ottawa, has 115,000 subscribers.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   A Rogers Communications official said the company already
has a stake of "less than 50%" in Skyline Cablevision, and
that the acquisition of the remaining shares from a group of
individuals in Ottawa would bring its stake to 100%.
   Toronto-based Rogers Communications, through its Rogers
Cablesystems Ltd. unit, has 1.6 million cable subscribers.
Rogers Communications also has interests in
telecommunications, broadcasting and mobile communications.
</TEXT>
