</HL>
<DATE>
07/05/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   F.ASP G.MES U.BA E.CAF F.ABI
</CO>
<IN>
AIRLINES (AIR)
AEROSPACE (ARO)
</IN>
<LP>
   Airbus Industrie said it signed a contract with French
airline Air Inter for delivery of seven Airbus Industrie
A321s and for options on another eight aircraft.
   In keeping with company policy, Airbus didn't disclose the
value of the contract. The latest published price for an A321
is between $40 million and $42 million.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Airbus said Air Inter also had exercised all of its
remaining options for A320s, bringing to 24 the number of
A320s Air Inter has ordered.
   The A321s will seat 210 passengers in an all-economy
layout, Airbus said. Both the A320s and the A321s will be
used for short routes.
   Airbus said total commitments for the A321 now stand at
185 from 10 customers. Combined firm orders for the A320 and
the A321 now total 607 from 28 customers.
   Airbus is a consortium of Aerospatiale of France,
Messerschmitt-Boelkow-Blohm G.m.b.H of West Germany, British
Aerospace PLC and Construcciones Aeronauticas S.A. of Spain.
